Translation from the viewpoint of semiotics, relations of translation with other meaning-generating processes, analysis of different types of translation phenomena.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the main ways and representatives of semiotic approaches to translation; to introduce theoretical concepts that can be applied for analysing different types of translation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course  1) is able to interpret translation from the viewpoint of semiotics as one of the main meaning-generating processes and can relate it to other meaning-generating processes such as semiosis, (meta-, auto-) communication, interpretation, different textual transformations; 2) knows the main authors, terms and concepts relevant for the relations between semiotics and translation; 3) is able to analyse translational phenomena, applying terms and concepts acquired and working independently with theoretical literature.
